pr_body:
This PR is in reference to the GSoC'20 project **Python3 bindings for InnerModel library**. Proposal is [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1o561DDcczCJ1l8a4ZLwdagMi2dN4MU4eFXdE3_7FAYI/edit?usp=sharing).

**WORK DONE**
- Ported the C++ class design to Python3
- Designed from scratch InnerModelViewer class in Python
- Enabled headless rendering in InnerModelViewer
- Enabled real-time control of a MultiLinkBody
- Implemented sensors like camera, IMU, pointcloud, laser
- Inline documentation in code

**WORK LEFT**
- Change the point of view of the debug window for the simulator using mouse action in InnerModelViewer
- More test cases for InnerModel lib

Stand-alone repo for the project is [here](https://github.com/ksakash/innermodel-python3).
The whole report for the code submission is [here](https://gist.github.com/ksakash/e3ea536981d9c8ab88c98766ff41d04b).

@ljmanso Pls review
